review_blob: Pours nice golden with small white head. Aroma is resinous/citrusy. Probably expected too much from this, based on all the positive reviews and the fact that I love a lot of the other Anchor beers. Overall a good beer, but nothing special.
On bottle from Vinmonopolet. Pours a nice dark brown colour. Good malt backbone here. Overall very enjoyable for the style.
